  <evidence rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Kinja does not provide any Personally Identifiable Information to third-party advertising companies Note however that if an advertiser asks Kinja to show an advertisement to users with certain characteristics for example women ages 18-24 or a segment of that group for example women ages 18-24 who have viewed certain categories of content and you respond to that advertisement the third-party advertising company may conclude that you have the characteristics of the audience that they are trying to reach</evidence>
